title: Were Biden’s Dogs Kicked Out of White House Due to Aggressive Behavior?
subtitle: The two German shepherds, Major and Champ, moved into the presidential mansion in late January.
author: Jessica Lee
vclaim: In early March 2021, U.S. President Joe Biden and first lady Jill Biden's two dogs were sent to their family home in Delaware because the youngest dog, Major, bit someone at the White House.
